(16,	1,	'2025-04-22 00:28:05',	'2025-04-22 00:28:05',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When we talk about the most powerful Force users in Star Wars history, names like Luke Skywalker, Yoda, and Darth Vader immediately come to mind. But there’s one figure who often flies under the radar — yet could have rivaled (or even surpassed) them all: <strong>Galen Marek</strong>, better known as <strong>Starkiller</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>First introduced in <em>Star Wars: The Force Unleashed</em> (2008), Starkiller was Darth Vader’s secret apprentice, trained in secret to overthrow Emperor Palpatine. But Starkiller was far from just another Sith acolyte. His raw connection to the Force and his unorthodox, brutal training made him arguably one of the most powerful Force wielders we’ve ever seen — even if much of his story is now part of <em>Legends</em> instead of <em>canon</em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Raw Force Power</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>Unlike Jedi who train for decades under strict codes, Starkiller’s training was harsh, emotional, and survival-driven. This gave him a <em>direct</em>, <em>unfiltered</em> connection to the Force. Starkiller didn’t just move objects with telekinesis — he <strong>brought down a Star Destroyer</strong> from orbit. While other Force users used the Force to push or pull small objects, Starkiller weaponized it on a galactic scale.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>Force lightning, mind control, enhanced physical abilities — he could do it all, and often all at once.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Potential Beyond Vader and Palpatine</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>Vader believed that Starkiller could <em>help him overthrow the Emperor</em>. This alone is telling. Vader, one of the most strategic and power-driven Sith Lords ever, saw <em>true</em> potential in his apprentice. Some even theorize that if Starkiller had fully embraced his dark power — or even found balance like later Jedi — he could have become the strongest Force user of his time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>And Palpatine? He was so threatened by Starkiller that he manipulated events to destroy him — <em>twice</em>. Even Palpatine feared what Starkiller could become.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Starkillers Potential',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'starkillers-potential',	'',	'',	'2025-04-28 17:54:00',	'2025-04-28 17:54:00',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:10052/?p=16',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(17,	1,	'2025-04-22 00:28:05',	'2025-04-22 00:28:05',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Galen possessed an unusually strong connection to the Force. His raw power as a toddler was such that Vader mistook his Force signature for that of a Jedi Master who far exceeded his father, Kento Marek, in power, even managing to telekinetically disarm the Dark Lord as they attempted to strike his father down.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Starkillers Potential',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'16-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2025-04-22 00:28:05',	'2025-04-22 00:28:05',	'',	16,	'http://localhost:10052/?p=17',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
