(89,	1,	'2025-04-28 21:19:37',	'2025-04-28 21:19:37',	'<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>Miranda, one of the five largest moons of Uranus, is a small, but fascinating world with a strikingly fractured surface that makes it stand out among the solar system’s moons. It has deep valleys, large ridges, and giant fault canyons, leading scientists to wonder: What caused this moon to look so unusual?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>Miranda’s appearance suggests that it has experienced severe geological activity. Some scientists believe that the moon was once shattered due to tidal forces caused by Uranus\' strong gravity, perhaps from a collision or internal instability. After being broken apart, the pieces could have re-accumulated, but the moon was never fully “reformed,” leaving it with a patchwork surface of older, heavily cratered terrain and younger, less-damaged regions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>The <strong>extreme tilt</strong> of Uranus, which causes its moons to be subjected to varying gravitational forces, likely played a role in Miranda\'s fractured features. This unusual history is why its surface appears so dramatically scarred, as if it\'s been pieced together from different parts of its past.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>Miranda remains one of the most intriguing moons in the solar system, offering clues about the violent history of moons around gas giants and the dynamic forces at play in our solar system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Miranda: The Moon with a Mysterious, Shattered Past',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'miranda-the-moon-with-a-mysterious-shattered-past',	'',	'',	'2025-04-28 21:20:46',	'2025-04-28 21:20:46',	'',	0,	'http://group-project.local/?p=89',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
